# Commit messages

Only when user asks commit message or create/run git commit.

[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

- Subject: `type(scope): imperative summary` — scope optional
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `build`, `ci`, `style`, `revert`
- Imperative after colon: "add", "fix", "update" — not "added", "adds", "adding"
- Subject max 72 chars; no trailing period
- Body only for why, breaking change, issue ref; wrap 72 chars
- Breaking: `!` after type/scope or `BREAKING CHANGE:` in body
- Concise; no diff restate, file laundry list, AI attribution

Examples:

```
fix(auth): reject expired session tokens
feat(api): add pagination to list endpoint
chore(deps): bump lockfile
```
